50|$|Walter P. Schuetze was Chief Accountant of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission during 1992-1995. He {{is known}} for being an {{advocate}} of <b>mark-to-market</b> accounting, which increases consistency between accounting statements' asset values and actual values of assets.|$|E
