50|$|The {{practice}} of mark to market as an accounting practice first developed among traders on futures exchanges during the 20th century. It {{was not until}} the 1980s that the practice spread to major banks and corporations, and beginning during the 1990s, <b>mark-to-market</b> accounting began to result in scandals.|$|E
